title: ULTRASOUND LEFT LOWER EXTREMITY VEINS

technique.description: Ultrasound images of the left lower extremity deep veins including the common femoral vein, junction to the common femoral vein with the great saphenous vein, proximal deep femoral vein, femoral vein, and popliteal vein acquired. Color and spectral Doppler ultrasound images also acquired. The fullest visualized extent of the aforementioned veins was interrogated.

impression: No deep venous thrombosis in the left lower extremity.
